    <section id="about">
      <h2>About Me</h2>
      <p><img src="/sites/default/files/IMG_4899_0.jpg" height="333" alt="Picture of Toshifumi Kamino" width="500"></p>
      <p id="about-text">Hi! I'm Toshifumi Kamino — a creative individual with both Norwegian and Japanese roots. My journey began in Japan, where I studied violin making and repair at a vocational school, gaining hands-on skills in crafting and restoring violins, violas, and cellos.</p>
      <p id="about-text">After graduating, I moved to Norway and attended a Folkehøyskole to explore my interest in hunting and fishing. Over time, my passion shifted toward digital creativity — especially web design and video editing.</p>
      <p id="about-text">I launched a personal blog using WordPress to share photos and videos, which I edit myself. This sparked a deep interest in IT and digital tools, motivating me to pursue further learning. I started with Cyberlink and later advanced to Adobe Premiere Pro and After Effects, gaining experience in basic editing, color grading, and smooth transitions.</p>
      <p id="about-text">In 2024, I joined a course called Digitale Talenter, where I deepened my knowledge of web development. I began with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, and progressed to modern frameworks like React and Next.js.</p>
      <p id="about-text">In parallel, I’ve been teaching myself 3D modeling using Blender. From creating simple shapes to building complex character models, this journey continues to inspire my curiosity and creativity.</p>
      <p id="about-text">I'm passionate about combining technology and creativity — and I'm excited to keep building, learning, and sharing my work with the world.</p>
    </section>

