    {# My Projects #}
<section id="projects">
  <h2>My Projects</h2>
  <div class="projects-grid">
    <div class="project-item">
      <img src="/sites/default/files/image0004.png" alt="Flag Quiz" width="300" height="225">
      <h3><a href="https://flag-quiz-orcin.vercel.app/">Flag Quiz</a></h3>
      <p id="projects-text">A React-based Flag Quiz web app built with Tailwind CSS that challenges users to identify 30 national flags per game. It features dark mode, real-time correct/incorrect sound effects, and a top-10 high-score leaderboard stored in localStorage.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="project-item">
      <img src="/sites/default/files/image0005.png" alt="Reversi Site" width="300" height="225">
      <h3><a href="https://reversi-site.vercel.app/">Reversi Game</a></h3>
      <p id="projects-text">A lightweight Reversi (Othello) web app built with Next.js 13, TypeScript, and Tailwind CSS v3. You play black; a simple CPU plays white by picking a random legal move. Auto-pass, game-over detection, restart, and subtle sound effects are included, all wrapped in a dark glass-card UI.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="project-item">
      <img src="/sites/default/files/Simple%20Note%20App.png" alt="Simple Note App" width="300" height="225">
      <h3><a href="https://simple-note-app-sage.vercel.app/">Simple Note App</a></h3>
      <p id="projects-text">A minimalist note-taking web app built with React and Tailwind CSS. Users can add and delete notes in real-time using a clean, responsive UI. The app features interactive button animations with shadow and press effects, and a styled textarea for comfortable writing. Designed for simplicity and speed, it's an ideal starting point for learning React component design and Tailwind-based UI styling.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="project-item">
      <img src="/sites/default/files/PortfplioReact.png" alt="Portfolio React" width="300" height="225">
      <h3><a href="https://portfolio-react-topaz-three.vercel.app/">Portfolio React</a></h3>
      <p id="projects-text">A simple portfolio website built with React. It features a clean layout with a navigation bar, self-introduction, project links, and contact details. This earlier project served as a personal introduction and a hub for linking other works, using plain CSS for styling and basic component structure.</p>
    </div>
